HR NO. 322 ENROLLED
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby create the Task Force on Second Degree Murder to
study, analyze, and evaluate the definition, application, and penalty structure of second
degree murder in Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall be composed of the
following members:
(1) The chairwoman of the House Committee on Administration of Criminal Justice
or her designee.
(2) One member of the Louisiana House of Representatives appointed by the
speaker.
(3) The secretary of the Department of Public Safety and Corrections or his
designee.
(4) The chairwoman of the Board of Pardons or her designee.
(5) The executive director of the committee on parole or his designee.
(6) The executive director of the Louisiana Sheriffs’ Association or his designee.
(7) The executive director of the Louisiana District Attorneys Association or his
designee.
(8) The state public defender or his designee.
(9) The executive director of the Louisiana Parole Project or his designee.
(10) The president of the Louisiana Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers, or
his designee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the chairman and vice chairman of the task force
shall be elected by a majority of the task force members at its first meeting, which shall be
called no later than September 1, 2026, and the members may select other officers as the task
force deems appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall meet at such times and
places as determined by its chair.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the task force constitutes a quorum
for the transaction of business. All official actions of the task force require the affirmative
vote of a majority of the members.
