BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
without compensation, except per diem or expenses reimbursement to which they may be
individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Rules of Order of the House of
Representatives or applicable Joint Rules shall apply to all meetings of the task force.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that meetings of the task force are subject to the
Open Meetings Law, R.S. 42:11 et seq., and records of the task force are subject to the
Public Records Law, R.S. 44:1 et seq.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall terminate following the
conclusion of its business or February 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall be staffed by the Department
of Public Safety and Corrections, which shall provide the necessary support and facilities
for the task force to perform its duties.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall submit a written report of
its findings and recommendations to the legislature no later than February 1, 2027.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to each
of the task force members provided in this Resolution.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall submit one print copy and
one electronic copy of any report produced pursuant to this Resolution to the David R.
Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S. 24:772.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
